GF grammars for CSE terminology

Aarne Ranta 2020

Prerequisites:

- download and install the GF Resource Grammar Library

- link to the sources of big dictionaries (temporary solution, should be avoidable in the future)

  ln -s <PATH-TO-gf-rgl>/src/english/
  ln -s <PATH-TO-gf-rgl>/src/swedish/

To make the translator grammar:

  gf -make -probs=CSETranslator.probs CSETranslatorEng.gf CSETranslatorSwe.gf

To test the translator grammar:

  $ gf -cshell CSETranslator.pgf
  > p -lang=CSETranslatorSwe -number=1 "efter kursen måste alla studenter skriva och läsa programkod" | l
  after course all students must write and read program code
  efter kursen måste alla studenter skriva och läsa programkod

OBSOLETE:

Then you can test this grammar as follows:

  $ gf CSEGrammarEng.gf CSEGrammarSwe.gf

  CSEGrammar> gr -cat=S | l
  this graphical goal wouldn't have wanted to be relevant
  det här grafiska målet skulle inte ha velat vara relevant

